How to configure elasticsearch standalone?
 Follow below steps to configure standalone elastickserach.
 1.once elastic search installation completed open the configuration file from below path
  /etc/elasticsearch/elasticsearch.yml
 2.Edit below line from file elasticsearch.yml
  cluster.name: mycluster1
  node.name: "My First Node"
  # network.host: 192.168.0.1
  Uncomment it and set the VPN IP to your server.
  network.host: x.x.x.x
  node.master: true
  node.data: true
  index.number_of_shards: 1
  index.number_of_replicas: 0
 3.Save and exit the file.
 4.Finally, start and enable the Elasticsearch service.
